caption: Sushi was decent but the are better Thai options nearby.
Delicious and affordable Thai cuisine with friendly service.
Pad Thai is delicious. Prices are extremely reasonable and customer service is top notch. Highly recommend

Tonight is the second time Dib cancels our order without notification. This is very unprofessional from them! Why accept the order and then decline it?? This is per Uber Eats and it was the restaurant who canceled it. After waiting for almost 45 mins and living just up the street why do this? I thought you all needed support and business? I am never trying this place again!
Great Maki rolls and Thai food!
Was pretty good.
Do you want soup and bright red LIPSTICK ON THE SPOON?  How does a server not notice that???
Delicious basil fried rice
Triple tuna was ok...kinda plain w a jalapeño for $15.
Honestly have only tried them for a quick take out lunch of pad Thai so cannot comment on their service and other dishes. This is a solid one though just the right amount of spice, tart, sweetness.
Been coming here for 10 years. Delicious,  fresh, awesome menu and service.  My go to. Yum. I'm here right now lol.

I've bought food from this place several times but it looks like they don't listen. I'm not that one person to make bad reviews but I think it's important they know what's happening. The chicken padthai they now served is just horrible. I think the Cook County Jail serves better noodles. These are dry, tasteless. I called them back and told them how bad these noodles were and they said "oh just say next time you don't want dry noodles". Seriously, I ordered padthai chicken not dry noodles. I've bought padthai chicken from other places and they're juicy. I was embarrassed to have my friends eat this food. I contemplated going back to the restaurant and have my money back but I just couldn't do it. Hopefully my review could help them improve this dish.  I will never buy anything from this place again.
Yummy food cash discount and takes orders on the phone.
Really good
The freshest sushi on the Northside! Ample portions and good service. Food is consistently delicious and there are no surprises. Have been many times, highly recommend.
This restaurant is no doubt one of the most pleasant place in the neighborhood. Every time I come there I am extremely happy.  Highly  recommended.
Support local businesses! I love this place! The prices are great! The food always great!

Last time I was here, I ordered the Hawaiian fried rice and added shrimp. While the rice tasted good, I was surprised by the amount of shrimp in the food - 3 pieces! I’m not greedy on these kind of things but there were few enough for me to notice. I think they could have added a bit more. The shrimp was also overcooked, almost rubbery. The rest of it was good though and Thai iced tea was nice.
Great service with great food. Highly recommend it, far best sushi all around. Thank you once again ;-)
Amazing sushi! Had a great experience!
food was very good!! They’re fast and clean, cashier was awesome and polite. Highly recommended. Thank you!
Worst sushi ever!
Food was delicious! Sushi was great. Nice presentation of it all. I will definitely return!
Red snapper is fabulous!!! Must try it!

This is my favorite sushi place in town. The Black & White Roll is the best😋. They are always friendly and since quarantine started I’ve been getting Dib delivered at least once a week. My order is always prepared quickly and correctly.
Ordered the crispy chicken green curry and the veggie red curry. Both dishes were amazing.Definitely be ordering again to try another dish.:)

Third time ordering this month. The food has NOT been what it used to be.  My Thai iced tea, twice had been over creamed! The fried rice, to much of some ingredient, twice. The pad se ew, the beef is overcooked and tough! The crab rangoons; no longer delicious; served semi warm and sometimes too crispy; not golden brown.  I’m so disappointed. Food just does not taste as well prepared and rushed food. I still love this place, I hope they prepare the food to be good.

I ordered from here last weekend and delivery was pretty quick. Ordered an assortment of rolls, nigiri, and the soft shell crab-- and crab rangoons. Everything tasted good and fresh. The rangoons were properly fried and particularly crab-y. No pics because the food only lasted a few moments upon entering my home. The prices are relatively less expensive than other the other and few sushi places in the area. I'm looking forward to eating here during better days, and trying some of their Thai dishes as well.
Food is always good.

This restaurant is no doubt one of the most pleasant place in the neighborhood. Every time I come there I am extremely happy. They manage their very high  level service and the topmost level of dishes  they give. You will be always satisfied with this place. Highly  recommended.
They serve large dishes and for fair prices. kind owner. Will visit again.
The lunch combo is fantastic.
I tried this spot in the past with my friend and I am addicted since then. I love the great ambience and tasty food and drinks. 5 stars from me.
Excellent.  Great lunch special.  Loved the sushi lunch special

It's a pretty small space so I would recommend making reservations! They have a really good selection of dishes, sushi, and drinks. The environment is fresh, clean, and sophisticated! The prices are fair. I really liked my visit to Dib and hope to come back soon!
Vegetable Pad Thai was tasty, fresh, satisfying and to 15 minutes for carry out.
Very well organised and accessible restaurant. They serve generous meals and for inexpensive rates. I loved the menu very much and the staff were super amiable and chatty. Highly recommended.

We like a lot hanging out. Last night we came to this excellent place which friends recommended to us. We passed a beautiful time there with delicious cooking and a courteous team and an impressive cook. We  added this venue in our list  and we will certainly visit again soon. We deeply recommend.

I adore this place! They offer splendid food, they have a rich menu, The chief cook in that spot is a specialist, I enjoy very much tasting all their food. The dishes are consistently tasty, the attitude towards the clients  is agreeable. I often go to  this place and I was never discontended. I recommend this place.
Great sushi place!
Excellent bargain

I often take my friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I visit this place often. This recommendation is always successful. The meals are delicious and the team is efficient and cooperative. always when we go to this place we pass a cheerful evening.  highly recommended.

The sushi portions at DIB are extremely small.  I even gave them a second try by informing them but they do not care one bit and so I will be taking my business elsewhere.  Down the street actually.  Much better to go two-four blocks away to Agami Sushi where the size of the Sashimi or Nigiri is never in question and Sushi quality + taste is always excellent.  Also, Dib is not authentic Japanese ( it's a Thai joint ) and it reflects in the quality and taste of their Sushi immediately.  You'll see a world of difference in regards to quality and taste when you order from Agami or any other authentic Japanese restaurant.  DIB should at the very least stop being so cheap with their portions for folks that are content about eating Sushi at a Thai place.
Favorite place to go for a semi-quick lunch in between meetings! Delicious food :)
Nice place nice people
Very nice tucked in place. The food selection was good and for a good price.
Excellent quality sushi and hospitality 👌
I love this place! Used to go there all the time when I lived in Chicago. Very hard to find something this good and reasonably priced in the suburbs. Never a disappointing dish.
Good soup, eggroll, sushi and pad thai! They have a special lunch menu also.
Great food. Typically fast services but occasionally under staffed but not often. Good prices.
The Dibs noodle, Chef specialty is one of the most horrible thing I've ever had in my life. Wide noodles in a sweet ketchup like sauce
Sea foods is very fresh 👍
Very tasty and all food was fresh and hot.  Menu prices higher than online posting.   Would eat again
Nice place

Hands down my favorite sushi and Thai restaurant in Uptown. Every roll is made with expert quality and the customer service is top notch, I've never once in eating here for 8 had a bad experience. It's definitely worth asking to sit and the bar to talk with the sushi chefs and watch them make the rolls, though anywhere else in this quaint corner restaurant is just as comfortable.
Off the chain
Eat there for a very long time and there pad thai is especially good, also try to order their lunch special.
Tastey right price
Great BYOB place. Awesome sushi....small place. Quaint....
Great food, great price, and BYOB!

it was the first time when we decided to visit this restaurant, we made an order with my wife and daughter and waited, after which they brought us sushi and we waited for the ordered soup TomYam (coconut milk) we were put on the table soup and I started eating it first, which is what my wife and I was completely satisfied with this soup, but when my wife started eating her portion of soup and after the first spoon I saw a small cockroach in soup !!!!!  THIS WAS A HORRIBLE CONDITION WHEN I UNDERSTOOD THAT I ALREADY HAVE EATED ALMOST HALF.  I felt bad and started to feel sick of what I saw on the plate of my wife, my wife and I immediately called the waiter and asked what was going on here ???  how it could happen, we were told not to shout so that other clients would not hear our complaints and would not hear anything else.  that's horrible!!  cockroaches in soup !!!  Oh my God!!!!  it was a bad experience and we want to tell about the following clients to be more careful.
I loved the sushi it was so delicious
Delicious food. Great serving sizes. The Mochi is bomb and so is the sushi!  Alot of places to sit. It's a great place to go with friends and hangout for lunch! 10/10 I definitely recommend!
Consistently good Thai food when dining in
Grilled chicken with curry
Great!
Fabulous little spot on Lawrence Ave. Their lunch specials are delicious--I tend to order the maki combo if I'm craving sushi, or red curry with tofu if I need my Thai fix. So yummy!

Come to this place just as walking past. The best sushi and sashimi I’ve ever had. So fresh well presented and tasty!! We were lucky enough to go during lunch time when they had the lunch time special, 3 course meal for next to no price!!! I wish I lived in Chicago so I could go more often!
Great lunch deal. Quick Take out.
Good food,and very accommodating. We were able to get fried rice with no vegetables and California roll with soy paper instead of sea weed. Everything tasted good and fresh

I call Dib(s)! A great experience in a chill Northside location with free... but limited... parking. Cozy and on the corner, this place features modern cuisine from Asian origins. Delicious and fresh, shout out to the chef, each plate was set with elegance and prepared carefully and quickly. Fast and friendly service. Great spot for a quick bite or lunch in the city.

I never eat here but I always get takeout. It's so delicious & filling and they have lunch specials on weekends. I'm giving 4 stars bc they charge $2 for beef in the pad Thai & online does not give the option of saying no meat or tofu.
The sushi is excellent! Very fresh. Served in a timely manner. Excellent service. Will return!
I was very impressed! I will be back! Sushi was "wow" fresh and cheap as fu#*. Service was top notch! I had appetizer,  2 entree, and dessert. Bill was only 37$ Thank you Dib!

Food and fast, friendly service always great every time I go! Never disappointed. They have great lunch specials too, but I definitely recommend the sushi rolls- crunchy shrimp roll is my favorite 😊. Their pick up ordering service is fast too, usually ready in 15mins. Highly recommend for everyone to try, you'll love it 🥰
Great food the soups are great👍
Delicious food

I looooove this place, the food is AMAZING! I love the green curry, and all the sushi dishes. The food is soooooo good, I can't find a better place with a more accommodating staff. My son loves it here, we've been here so many times. I love this!
Nice Thai at a good price.
Great prices and nice staff
Dib is small, quaint and delicious. Exceptional prices. Delivery available is a plus.
This use to be my old jobs go to restaurant.  It gets super packed at lunch but is the best Thai in the close walkable distance
The most underrated lunch spot in all of uptown. The service. Is always great and the sushi is on point
Great service and food. One of the best Thai restaurants in Uptown.

Dib was absolutely fantastic. The fish tasted fresh, my hot green tea was constantly refilled (without having to ask!), the taro custard was warm and pleasant, and the service was delightful. I can't wait to go back! Of note: they have a lunch menu that is served until 3 PM. There isn't any sashimi on it (aka it's still full price), but they have some great combos. Expect a 12-20 dollar bill for one person with tip.
Tasty food fast friendly service. The Chia Iced Tea is to die for!

This is my main go-to place for inexpensive yet very tasty sushi. If you use their own online ordering system you also get great perks such as extra appetizers etc. It's the Uptown neighborhood staple. Try it if you're ever around!

Today was my first time here.   I really enjoyed the fried tofu and garlic chicken.   The portions and prices were very reasonable.  The service was good too.  I will be back to explore the extensive menu!!

Great selection of sushi and great taste!
Great food!

Loved it.....my recent love for sushi was more than full filled here.
Great place but NOWHERE NEAR downtown Chicago !!

Small restaurant with authentic and delicious Thai food, sushi and quick service. Bear in mind that there is no public restroom. The location is ideal, as it's along a safe and active, though not terribly congested, strip of downtown Chicago. It is directly across the street from the newly renovated Aragon Ballroom.
Our go-to sushi and Tahoe delivery place. Always super fast and yummy.
I recommend TAKE OUT!!! SUPER FAST SERVICE! Great sushi, noodles and appetizers ♥
Good service and food. Great curry. Fair prices.

Cute little restaurant with sushi and Thai lunch specials. Lunch specials come with appetizer,  soup and entree I I add a coke and a 15-20% tip and eat for under $12!

While taking a break from packing, I ordered delivery from here and I was very excited to try this place.  Within minutes, my food was at my door and the food was nice and hot. Wow! Great service!  Soup: miso soup  Entree: beef teriyaki with potato salad, garden salad, and white rice. The beef was tender and the teriyaki had such nice flavor. The potato salad was light and did not taste like the usual potato salad, which was nice.  It also had thin strips of seaweed, which worked very well. Garden salad had very thin strips of carrots and radish, spinach, arugela, and light salad dressing.  Dessert: chocolate mochi  I really enjoyed this! Every thing tasted great and I will definitely be back.

Delicious sushi and thai food. I've been coming since I was an intern in the area back in 2015 and I always take my friends here. Even coming from the suburbs is easy because they have free parking! WARNING the spicy tuna is actually spicy  :)
My go to Thai restaurant.. love their banana wonton ice cream!!
This rating is only for Tasty Thai  menu. I have not tried the sushi here. A big plus is free parking in this area.
Enjoyed uptown but no sake!
The food was okay. The service was great!

The sushi was dry and not that taste. I was brought here by someone that lives near here, but i would say this person will eat anything and will disagree with me.  It's very hard to find good sushi in the city. But when I do find that place it will be my #1 go to place.

Lovvvve this place. Tasty, affordable, and friendly staff.  The place is rather small so seating (especially for groups) can be limited but delivery and take out are available.  If you're picking up and walking your dog, they'll even come outside to take your money and give you your order 👍

Friendly staff, good food. My complaint is that I wanted some really spicy Thai food. I asked them to make it very spicy, and I got barely spicy. This happens to me a lot, though, at Asian restaurants. Still, it was good curry.

Amazing Thai fusion spot. Their lunch specials are really cheap, and great quality and quantity!
Good service and kind staff. BYOB is always nice, but the sushi doesn't stand out in flavor.

I LOVED this place for a few years. Went once or sometimes twice a week. Until last week. I went to sit at my usual table and there was a giant bug (yes the worst kind of bug for restaurants) hanging out on the table next to mine. I left :( I love that place, such amazing service and friendly people but unfortunately I cannot go back. My tummy turns a little each time i think about it.
This is our sushi restaurant of choice where we live. Always great service and great sushi! We typically eat here a couple times a month and always enjoy it!

Omg my best friend and i were looking for a sushi restaurant and stumbled on Dib Sushi Bar. Not only was the presentation of the food beautiful, it was delicious. Our waitress was attentive and informative. My only regret that i live in Indiana and cannot frequent the restaurant as often as i like.

Had some sushi easily on par with some of the better places in Seattle and NYC. Was not busy on a Monday night with plenty of seating. Prices were also moderate with some great options on the menu for rolls or sushi/sashimi platters. I HIGHLY recommend the sake don (salmon sashimi over rice as pictured).

Delicious food and very friendly staff and prices. Also, it's just cozy)

Dib has essentially become my local spot due to its proximity to my apartment. The pad thai is wonderful (tip, order it with extra sauce!). But my absolute favorite is their Tom Yum sushi roll. It tastes just like a bowl of Tom Yum soup! The dining area is on the smaller side, but has a great vibe. It's good for small groups or more intimate dinners. BYOB!

The quality is on par with basic - but not excellent - Thai food. Unfortunately it's not cheap, and the space is pretty small. However, it does have a free parking lot for drivers and does have a nice atmosphere.
Great food for the price point, and great ambiance!  One of my go-to places in the neighborhood.
Not the best, but not the worst either. Just average.
Excellent sushi and great entrees. I always order extra for take out.

good

love the Thai curries. Avocado salad is also a favorite.
its hot
Best Thai curries. Awesome sushi. I go here often and I've never had a bad experience. Everyone I take here loves it.
Awesome service. Drunken Noodles with Shrimp is great.

I have never actually been inside, but I order delivery via GrubHub fairly frequently, and I'm always happy with the food and service. I particular I love the crab rangoon and Black and White Maki. I also really like their massaman curry, although it is not spicy--which could be a plus for some people, but I like more heat. They did give me some hot pepper sauce with my order, though, so I was able to customize a bit.

I love this place. Out of what seems like 100 Thai places in the city, this one really stands out to me as the best. It's on a quiet, unassuming corner in uptown, but it has some of the best Thai food I've had.  It's a small place with a modern atmosphere and friendly staff. My favorite dish is their basil fried rice, but I've also had several noodle dishes and curries, and all have been delightful. None are too greasy or lacking flavor as I've had at other places. They also have great lunch specials. This place is great for quick takeout, a weekend dinner date, and even groups.  A friend recommended this place to me right when I moved to Chicago 4 years ago, and I've been recommending it to others ever since.
Nice atmosphere. Solid food.

I have been going to this restaurant for over 5 years. It is by far the best sushi place! The presentation of the dishes, the quality, even the service is great. The location is not the greatest but it is worth going. Their shrimp friend rice is the most fresh, their tom kha soup is the best in town and crab rangoons? forget it! 5 stars for me!
A nice quiet lunch and great service.

The sushi was delicious and the delivery was prompt but my miso soup was just really...bad. It was flavorless and the seaweed was chewy almost. I'd definitely order from here again I'd just skip the miso soup.
Small place but very delicious with good specials. BYOB is always a plus.
Very nice place. Will try it again.
